peopleAlsoAsk.question: How do you determine the value of a lithograph?
peopleAlsoAsk.snippet: Look for a watermark or signature. Value of the print can also be influenced by the number of the print if the individual was a part of a series. This will be indicated at the bottom of the print and appear as a fraction indicating the number of the print out of the total number in the series.

peopleAlsoAsk.question: What is the difference between a lithograph and an original lithograph?
peopleAlsoAsk.snippet: Most modern lithographs are signed and numbered to establish an edition. An offset lithograph, also known as a limited edition print, is a reproduction by a mechanical process, in which the artist has in no way contributed to the process of making an original print: that is, he has not designed the plate.
